# `pg.Color(r, g, b)`

Creates a new color with the given
r=red, g=green, b=blue.

255 -> Full, 0 -> None.

## ex
So `pg.Color(255, 0, 0)` will give you really bright
red <span class="swatch" style="background-color: #F00"></span>, since it's only red and it's at max value.

## ex
So `pg.Color(255, 255, 255)` will give you bright white.
<span class="swatch" style="background-color: #FFF"></span>
(White is a mixture of all colors when working with displays.)
